==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catarrh
<hw>Ca*tarrh"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>catarrhus</ets>, Gr. <?/, <?/, a running down, rheum, fr. <?/;
<grk>kata`</grk> down + <?/ to flow. See <er>Stream</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An inflammatory affection of any mucous membrane,
in which there are congestion, swelling, and an alteration in the
quantity and quality of mucus secreted; <as>as, <ex>catarrh</ex> of the
stomach; <ex>catarrh</ex> of the bladder</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In America, the term <ex>catarrh</ex> is applied
especially to a chronic inflammation of, and hypersecretion fron, the
membranes of the nose or air passages; in England, to an acute
influenza, resulting a cold, and attended with cough, thirst, lassitude,
and watery eyes; also, to the cold itself.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catarrhal</ent>⟦br⟧
